-- Japanese Government to Sell 3% Stake in NTT to Boost Finances, Nikkei Says
-- B y   M a k i k o   K i t a m u r a
-- 2010-11-21T02:25:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-21/japanese-government-to-sell-3-stake-in-ntt-to-boost-finances-nikkei-says.html
The Japanese government plans to
sell a 3 percent stake in Nippon Telegraph & Telephone Corp. for
about 184 billion yen ($2.2 billion) to boost state finances,
the Nikkei newspaper said today.  The government held 530 million NTT shares, equivalent to a
36.62 percent stake, as of the end of March, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Makiko Kitamura in Tokyo at 
